02:59.375 --> 03:01.735
Excuse me.

03:03.295 --> 03:06.415
Come on, honey, let's
get you ready for bed.

03:18.625 --> 03:20.715
I am no one special,

03:20.755 --> 03:23.695
just a common man
with common thoughts.

03:23.725 --> 03:25.995
I've led a common life.

03:26.035 --> 03:27.935
There are no monuments
dedicated to me.

03:27.965 --> 03:31.065
And my name
will soon be forgotten.

03:31.105 --> 03:32.905
But in one respect,

03:32.935 --> 03:36.465
I've succeeded as gloriously
as anyone who ever lived.

03:36.505 --> 03:38.605
- Looking good, Duke.
- Feeling good.

03:38.645 --> 03:40.405
I've loved another
with all my heart

03:40.445 --> 03:44.475
and soul and for me
that has always been enough.

03:44.515 --> 03:45.915
How's it hanging, Harry?

03:45.955 --> 03:48.645
I keep trying to die,
but they won't let me.

03:48.685 --> 03:50.715
Well, you can't
have everything.

03:53.895 --> 03:55.125
Big day today.

03:55.165 --> 03:57.855
You say that every day,
you old devil.

03:59.235 --> 04:01.195
It's a lovely day
outside.

04:01.235 --> 04:03.465
Let's take a walk.

04:03.505 --> 04:04.565
I don't think so.

04:04.605 --> 04:06.905
Well, we've got to get
you out of this room.

04:06.935 --> 04:08.535
Come on now, honey.
Some fresh air

04:08.575 --> 04:11.005
- would do you good.
- Hello.

04:12.815 --> 04:15.275
I'm sorry,
it's not a good day.

04:15.315 --> 04:17.285
I don't think
she's up for anything.

04:17.315 --> 04:18.475
Hello?

04:20.315 --> 04:24.315
This is Duke,
he's come to read to you.

04:24.355 --> 04:26.625
Read?

04:27.855 --> 04:30.695
No.
I don't know.

04:30.725 --> 04:34.795
Oh, come on,
you'll like him, he's very funny.

04:46.515 --> 04:47.845
Ahh...

04:49.285 --> 04:53.215
All right now,
where did we leave off?

04:53.255 --> 04:56.585
Oh, yeah, yeah,
it was the night of the carnival.

04:56.625 --> 04:59.755
"Noah, was there with his friends,
Fin and Sarah."

04:59.795 --> 05:02.985
- Noah?
- That's where they met...

05:03.025 --> 05:05.125
June 6th, 1940.

05:06.565 --> 05:08.465
Allie was
17 years old.

05:09.005 --> 05:11.235
- Little man wins a prize.
- Damn!

05:11.275 --> 05:13.505
- Thank you for playing.
- Ha, you're real funny.

05:13.535 --> 05:14.805
Man, I clobbered
that thing.

05:14.845 --> 05:16.805
I'm tellin' you,
these games are fixed.

05:16.845 --> 05:18.465
- Hello.
- How are you?

05:18.515 --> 05:20.445
Hi, what's your name?

05:20.475 --> 05:22.175
Step right up here.

05:22.215 --> 05:24.405
Over the hook, yeah.

05:28.485 --> 05:31.515
- Who's this girl with Sara?
- Her name's Allie Hamilton.

05:31.555 --> 05:33.995
She's here for the summer
with her family.

05:34.025 --> 05:35.325
Dad's got more
money than God.

05:35.365 --> 05:37.455
- Hi, Fin!
- Hi, honey.

05:37.495 --> 05:40.295
Look, I won you a prize.

05:40.335 --> 05:43.665
Oh, Fin, thank you!

05:45.675 --> 05:48.075
- Oww!
- Yeah.

05:48.105 --> 05:49.865
Hey great, huh?

05:49.905 --> 05:51.735
Hey Allie, you want
some cotton candy?

05:51.775 --> 05:53.805
- Umm, okay.
- That would be so much fun.

05:55.645 --> 05:58.245
You only get
one chance, son.

05:58.285 --> 06:00.645
- You want to dance with me?
- No.

06:00.685 --> 06:03.815
- Why not?
- 'Cause I don't want to.

06:03.855 --> 06:06.845
Noah, she's with us.

06:06.895 --> 06:10.795
Hey Allie, you want
to ride the Ferris wheel?

06:10.825 --> 06:12.355
- I'd love to.
- All right.

06:12.395 --> 06:14.025
Excuse me.

06:15.305 --> 06:16.855
Excuse me.

06:20.935 --> 06:23.845
- Noah Calhoun.
- What?

06:23.875 --> 06:26.635
Works down at the lumber yard
with Fin.

06:26.675 --> 06:28.835
Oh...

06:28.885 --> 06:31.845
Did you see he was standing like
two inches away from my face?

06:31.885 --> 06:34.015
Yeah, I saw.
That's Noah, though.

06:35.725 --> 06:37.275
You know I'm surprised
he even came over.

06:37.325 --> 06:38.655
I think he likes you.

06:58.775 --> 07:00.475
Hey what... jerk...

07:00.515 --> 07:03.875
Get off me.
Don't touch me.

07:03.915 --> 07:05.975
- Hey!
- Well, I... ugh!

07:06.015 --> 07:08.005
- What are you doing?
- Hey, you can't do that!

07:08.055 --> 07:09.745
I'll pay you
when I get down, Tommy.

07:09.785 --> 07:11.585
I'm Noah Calhoun.

07:11.625 --> 07:13.715
- So?!
- So, it's really nice to meet you.

07:13.755 --> 07:16.315
- Allie, who is this guy?
- I don't know, Noah Calhoun.

07:16.365 --> 07:18.795
- I would really like to take you out.
- Friend! Do you mind?

07:20.535 --> 07:23.435
You can't sit more than two people
in a chair, Noah.

07:23.465 --> 07:24.935
Okay, Tommy,
all right.

07:27.975 --> 07:30.565
Get down, Noah,
you're gonna kill yourself!

07:30.605 --> 07:31.805
Noah, cut it out.

07:31.845 --> 07:33.505
Now, will you
go out with me?

07:33.545 --> 07:35.205
What?

07:35.245 --> 07:37.185
- No.
- No?

07:37.215 --> 07:38.545
- No.
- No?

07:38.585 --> 07:40.245
Hey pal,
she just told you.

07:40.285 --> 07:41.375
Why not?

07:41.425 --> 07:43.415
I don't know,
because I don't want to.

07:43.455 --> 07:44.475
Noah!

07:44.525 --> 07:46.855
What? Well, you leave me
no other choice then.

07:47.955 --> 07:49.085
Oh my God.

07:49.125 --> 07:50.115
I'm not kidding.

07:50.165 --> 07:51.895
- Noah, stop fooling around.
- What are you doing?

07:51.935 --> 07:54.335
- Noah, grab the bar.
- I'm gonna ask you one more time.

07:54.365 --> 07:55.955
Will you...

07:56.005 --> 07:58.735
- or will you not go out with me?
- Noah, you best come on.

07:58.775 --> 08:01.675
- God damn, my hand's slipping.
- Then grab the bar, you idiot.

08:01.705 --> 08:04.435
- Not until she agrees.
- Ah, go on out with him, honey.

08:04.475 --> 08:06.675
- Okay, okay, fine,
I'll go out with you.

08:06.715 --> 08:07.975
- What?
- No, don't do me any favors.

08:08.015 --> 08:09.345
No, no. I want to.

08:09.385 --> 08:10.715
- You want to? You want to?
- Yes!

08:10.745 --> 08:12.715
- Say it.
- I want to go out with you.

08:12.755 --> 08:15.345
- Say it again.
- I want to go out with you.

08:15.385 --> 08:17.715
All right, all right
we'll go out.

08:17.755 --> 08:20.525
You think
you're so smart, don't you?

08:20.555 --> 08:22.225
That wasn't funny,
Noah, you idiot!

08:22.265 --> 08:25.695
No, it's okay,
I'll take care of this.

08:25.735 --> 08:27.425
What are you doing?

08:27.465 --> 08:28.455
Please don't do that.

08:28.505 --> 08:30.025
Please don't do that, Allie.

08:30.065 --> 08:31.795
I can't believe...

08:31.835 --> 08:33.465
Oh God.

08:35.304 --> 08:37.075
You're not so cocky now,
are ya?

08:37.105 --> 08:38.975
I'm gonna get you for that.

08:39.015 --> 08:41.414
Ah, maybe you will,
maybe you won't.

08:43.985 --> 08:47.285
- Did he say anything to you?
- Oh, yeah, will you look at that?

08:47.315 --> 08:49.215
It's that girl from the Carnival,
right?

08:51.825 --> 08:53.725
Do you remember me?

08:53.755 --> 08:56.245
Yeah, sure,
Mr. Underwear, was it?

08:56.295 --> 08:58.025
- Well, I...
- How could I forget.

08:58.065 --> 08:59.555
Yeah, I wanted to clear
that up with you,

08:59.595 --> 09:01.085
because
I'm really sorry about that.

09:01.135 --> 09:02.425
It was a really stupid thing
to do...

09:02.465 --> 09:04.055
crawl up a Ferris wheel
to talk to somebody.

09:04.105 --> 09:06.005
But I had
to be next to you.

09:06.035 --> 09:08.195
I was being
drawn to you.

09:11.245 --> 09:13.675
Oh... oh, jeez,
what a line!

09:13.715 --> 09:16.075
You use that
on all the girls?

09:16.115 --> 09:17.845
- No.
- Right.

09:17.885 --> 09:20.185
I saw you the other night
with little Miss Ribbons.

09:20.215 --> 09:21.875
- What are you doing tonight?
- What?

09:21.925 --> 09:23.945
Or tomorrow night,
or this weekend, whatever.

09:23.985 --> 09:25.925
- Why?
- Why? Our date.

09:25.955 --> 09:27.215
What date?

09:27.255 --> 09:28.985
- The date that you agreed to.
- No...

09:29.025 --> 09:31.225
Yes, you did.
You promised and you swore it.

09:31.265 --> 09:33.025
Well, I guess
I changed my mind.

09:34.635 --> 09:36.995
Look, I know you get some dirty guy
coming up to you

09:37.035 --> 09:38.555
on the street...
you don't know him.

09:38.605 --> 09:40.435
You don't know me,
but I know me.

09:42.105 --> 09:43.835
And when I see something
that I like,

09:43.875 --> 09:46.205
I gotta ha...
I love it.

09:46.245 --> 09:48.305
I go... I mean,
I go crazy for it.

09:48.345 --> 09:51.115
Okay, what are you
talking about?

09:51.145 --> 09:52.345
Well, you.

09:53.515 --> 09:55.215
Oh, you're good.

09:55.255 --> 09:56.885
- What?
- You're good.

09:56.925 --> 09:59.395
- No. No, you're getting me wrong.
- You're good. You are.

09:59.425 --> 10:00.945
- You're fantastic.
- I'm not.

10:00.995 --> 10:02.855
You really are.
I'm impressed.

10:02.895 --> 10:06.195
- I'm not usually like this, I'm sorry.
- Oh, yes, you are.

10:06.235 --> 10:08.325
I can be fun,
if you want...

10:08.365 --> 10:11.855
pensive, uh, smart,

10:11.905 --> 10:14.635
uh, superstitious,
brave.

10:14.675 --> 10:17.605
And uh... I can be light on my feet.

10:17.645 --> 10:20.205
I could be
whatever you want.

10:20.245 --> 10:22.975
You just tell me what you want
and I'll be that for you.

10:24.115 --> 10:25.545
You're dumb.

10:27.815 --> 10:29.185
I could be that.

10:32.095 --> 10:34.085
Come on, one date.
What's it gonna hurt?

10:34.125 --> 10:35.785
Umm...
I don't think so.

10:35.825 --> 10:37.655
Well, what I can I do
to change your mind?

10:37.695 --> 10:39.635
Guess you'll figure
something out.

10:41.635 --> 10:44.105
- You sure she's coming?
- Relax, pal, it's all set up.

10:44.135 --> 10:45.655
We're meeting her
for the late show.

10:45.705 --> 10:47.535
Look... what did
I tell you? Come on.

10:53.175 --> 10:56.615
Oh my goodness,
what a coincidence!

10:56.645 --> 10:58.375
I need to talk to you
for a second.

10:58.415 --> 11:02.185
- He's here!
- Allie, you remember Noah, don't you?

11:02.225 --> 11:03.205
- Yes, I remember.
- Yeah.

11:03.255 --> 11:05.185
- Come here.
- Fin!

11:05.225 --> 11:06.885
- Hi.
- Hi.

11:06.925 --> 11:09.255
- It's nice to see you again.
- You too.

11:09.295 --> 11:11.455
- You look great.
- Aw, thanks.

11:11.495 --> 11:13.195
Really, really great.

11:13.235 --> 11:14.925
You do look great.
You look great.

11:14.965 --> 11:18.365
And I know I look great,
so could we please go see this movie?

11:18.405 --> 11:21.165
- The show's about to start.
- After you.

11:21.205 --> 11:23.835
You come back here,
Li'I Abner.

11:23.875 --> 11:26.435
You ain't gonna catch me,
Daisy Mae!

11:26.475 --> 11:28.745
It's Sadie Hawkins Day,
I'm supposed to catch you!

11:28.785 --> 11:30.505
I'm faster than you.

11:32.515 --> 11:34.285
No, No!

11:34.315 --> 11:36.515
I'll get you!

11:37.685 --> 11:39.625
I'm going get...

11:39.655 --> 11:41.125
Here I come!

11:41.155 --> 11:43.655
You better run fast!

11:53.275 --> 11:55.265
You ketchum Polecat
far and squar.

12:01.545 --> 12:04.205
Wait for me.

12:04.245 --> 12:06.275
What happened
in that movie?

12:07.615 --> 12:09.785
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

12:11.255 --> 12:13.385
- What are you guys doing?
- Want to walk with me?

12:13.425 --> 12:14.415
Yeah, what's going on?

12:14.455 --> 12:15.895
- Yeah.
- We're gonna walk.

12:15.925 --> 12:18.415
Do you guys
love each other?

12:18.465 --> 12:20.765
Huh?
Oh, I get it.

12:20.795 --> 12:23.595
- You guys do love each other.
- Don't do anything I wouldn't do.

12:23.635 --> 12:24.725
Okay, good bye.

12:24.765 --> 12:27.265
All right, all right.

12:31.345 --> 12:33.405
That was fun.

12:35.345 --> 12:37.745
I haven't seen a movie
in ages.

12:37.785 --> 12:39.545
Really?

12:39.585 --> 12:42.385
Not since
I was a little kid.

12:42.425 --> 12:44.015
What?

12:44.055 --> 12:45.855
No, I..

12:45.895 --> 12:48.485
I'm busy, you know,
I don't have a lot of time.

12:49.795 --> 12:51.225
You're busy?

12:51.265 --> 12:54.855
I have a very
strict schedule.

12:54.895 --> 12:56.665
My days are all
planned out.

12:56.705 --> 13:00.935
I get up in the morning... breakfast,
math tutor, Latin tutor, lunch,

13:00.975 --> 13:04.705
tennis lessons, dance lessons...
sometimes both...

13:04.745 --> 13:08.575
French tutor, piano lesson,
then I eat dinner.

13:08.615 --> 13:10.605
And after dinner
I spend time with my family.

13:10.645 --> 13:13.445
And then I... I catch up
on some reading.

13:19.125 --> 13:20.925
Sounds like the road
to success.

13:20.955 --> 13:22.625
Oh, you bet.

13:22.665 --> 13:24.325
We're applying
to all these colleges...

13:24.365 --> 13:28.825
umm... Radcliffe, Sarah Lawrence...
those are the ones we want.

13:30.505 --> 13:33.405
- And who's we?
- What?

13:33.435 --> 13:35.535
You just said,
"The ones that we want."

13:35.575 --> 13:37.235
Oh, Mom and Daddy.

13:37.275 --> 13:39.075
We decide
everything together.

13:40.445 --> 13:42.645
Everything?

13:42.685 --> 13:44.345
No, not everything.

13:44.385 --> 13:46.115
But the important
things, yes.

13:47.715 --> 13:50.955
And then everything else,
you get to decide all by yourself?

13:52.795 --> 13:55.655
- Don't be rude.
- I'm sorry.

13:58.225 --> 14:01.285
Just trying to figure out
what you do for fun.

14:01.335 --> 14:04.195
What do you mean?

14:04.235 --> 14:06.605
I mean...

14:06.635 --> 14:08.235
I don't know,
I mean all those things

14:08.275 --> 14:10.835
are things you
have to do, right?

14:10.875 --> 14:14.745
So what do you do
because you want to?

14:14.775 --> 14:16.905
I just told ya.

14:19.985 --> 14:21.645
I don't know.

14:21.685 --> 14:24.175
This surprises me.

14:24.225 --> 14:25.515
Why?

14:25.555 --> 14:29.015
I just always figured
you were kinda...

14:29.065 --> 14:30.855
Kinda what?

14:30.895 --> 14:32.195
Just...

14:34.235 --> 14:37.065
- Free.
- What?

14:37.105 --> 14:38.625
Free.

14:40.905 --> 14:43.435
I am free.

14:43.475 --> 14:46.235
You don't seem like it.

14:46.275 --> 14:48.245
Well, I am.

14:50.385 --> 14:52.375
Come here,
I want to show you something.

14:52.415 --> 14:56.085
- Noah, what are you doing?
- Just come on.

14:56.125 --> 14:59.555
- You're gonna get run over.
- By all the cars?

15:07.335 --> 15:08.925
My Dad and I used
to come out here

15:08.965 --> 15:12.695
and lay down and watch
the lights change.

15:12.735 --> 15:15.725
And watch them go
from green to red to yellow.

15:17.375 --> 15:20.135
You could try it,
if you wanted to.

15:20.175 --> 15:22.575
- No.
- Why not?

15:22.615 --> 15:25.375
Because I don't know...
will you just get up?

15:25.415 --> 15:27.815
That's your problem,
you know that?

15:29.155 --> 15:30.675
You don't do
what you want.

15:39.095 --> 15:40.625
Okay.

15:57.845 --> 15:59.815
What happens
if a car comes?

15:59.855 --> 16:01.545
- We die.
- What?

16:01.585 --> 16:03.525
Just relax.
Just trust.

16:03.555 --> 16:05.985
You need to learn
how to trust.

16:07.695 --> 16:09.155
Okay.

16:12.235 --> 16:13.955
Painting.

16:13.995 --> 16:16.555
You asked me
what I do for me.

16:16.605 --> 16:20.335
- What now?
- I love to paint.

16:20.375 --> 16:23.565
Yeah?

16:25.715 --> 16:29.645
Most of the time, I have all these
thoughts bouncing around in my head.

16:29.685 --> 16:32.985
But with a brush
in my hand,

16:33.015 --> 16:35.785
the world just gets
kinda quiet.

16:43.865 --> 16:45.525
Get out of the street!

16:54.375 --> 16:55.395
Are you okay?

16:58.105 --> 17:00.205
Why are you laughing?

17:03.515 --> 17:05.944
Oh, that was fun.

17:10.355 --> 17:12.055
Do you want
to dance with me?

17:13.755 --> 17:14.785
Sure.

17:17.765 --> 17:19.325
Now?

17:19.365 --> 17:20.994
Here?

17:21.035 --> 17:23.625
Not supposed to dance
in the middle of the street.

17:23.665 --> 17:26.765
Who said dance
in the street?

